{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD"]]},"metadata":{"title":"FAQ","modules":[{"name":"FlyHUD"}],"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article"},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/faq","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/flyhud\/faq"]}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Reference","anchor":"Reference","identifiers":["doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/privacy","doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/benchmark","doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/release-notes","doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/CHANGELOG"]}],"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"General","text":"General","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"anchor":"What-is-the-difference-between-FlyHUD-FlyIndicatorHUD-and-FlyProgressHUD","text":"What is the difference between FlyHUD, FlyIndicatorHUD, and FlyProgressHUD?","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"FlyHUD"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" — The core module containing the "},{"code":"HUD","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" class, layout system, animations,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and background views. This is all you need for system indicators and custom views."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"FlyIndicatorHUD"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" — Provides custom activity indicator styles (ring clip, ball spin,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"circle stroke, arc dot). Depends on FlyHUD."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"FlyProgressHUD"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" — Provides custom progress view styles (bar, round, annular, pie)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Depends on FlyHUD."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can import only what you need. All three are independent of each other.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Why-was-it-renamed-from-LPHUD-to-FlyHUD","text":"Why was it renamed from LPHUD to FlyHUD?","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The library was renamed in version 1.5.6 to better reflect its nature: “Fly” implies","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"fast, efficient, and flexible — consistent with the real-time nature of a HUD.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Does-FlyHUD-support-SwiftUI","text":"Does FlyHUD support SwiftUI?","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Yes! The ","type":"text"},{"code":"FlyHUDSwiftUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" module provides native SwiftUI support with declarative modifiers:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["import FlyHUDSwiftUI","","MyView()","    .hudLoading(isPresented: $isLoading, label: \"Loading...\")"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"See ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/swiftui-integration","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" for complete documentation covering all API layers.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Installation","text":"Installation","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"anchor":"Which-module-should-I-import","text":"Which module should I import?","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Need"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Import"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"System spinner + custom views only"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"FlyHUD","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"SwiftUI declarative modifiers"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"FlyHUDSwiftUI","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Custom indicator animations"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"FlyHUD","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" + "},{"code":"FlyIndicatorHUD","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Custom progress styles"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"FlyHUD","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" + "},{"code":"FlyProgressHUD","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All features"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All three"}],"type":"paragraph"}]]],"header":"row","type":"table"},{"anchor":"Can-I-use-only-CocoaPods-subspecs","text":"Can I use only CocoaPods subspecs?","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Yes. Use subspecs to minimize dependencies:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"ruby","type":"codeListing","code":["pod 'FlyHUD', :subspecs => ['FlyHUD']           # Core only","pod 'FlyHUD', :subspecs => ['FlyIndicatorHUD']  # Core + indicators","pod 'FlyHUD', :subspecs => ['FlyProgressHUD']   # Core + progress"]},{"anchor":"Why-do-I-get-No-such-module-FlyHUD-in-my-Xcode-project","text":"Why do I get “No such module ‘FlyHUD’” in my Xcode project?","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Ensure you have:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Added the SPM package dependency correctly"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Added the library product to your target’s “Frameworks, Libraries, and Embedded Content”"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Cleaned build folder (Shift+Cmd+K) and rebuilt"}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"anchor":"Usage","text":"Usage","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"anchor":"Why-does-my-HUD-stay-on-screen-forever","text":"Why does my HUD stay on screen forever?","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Every ","type":"text"},{"code":"show()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" must be paired with a ","type":"text"},{"code":"hide()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". Common causes:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Forgetting to call "},{"code":"hide()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" on error paths"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Calling "},{"code":"hide()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" on a different HUD instance"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Using "},{"code":"isCountEnabled = true","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" without matching show\/hide pairs"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"Why-does-my-HUD-appear-behind-other-views","text":"Why does my HUD appear behind other views?","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"HUD is added as a subview of the view you specify. Ensure no other views are added","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"after the HUD, or call ","type":"text"},{"code":"view.bringSubviewToFront(hud)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Why-doesnt-the-keyboard-guide-work","text":"Why doesn’t the keyboard guide work?","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Keyboard guide is iOS-only (not available on tvOS or visionOS)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Ensure "},{"code":"HUD.keyboardGuide","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"code":"hud.keyboardGuide","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is set to "},{"code":".center()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"code":".bottom()","type":"codeVoice"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The keyboard must actually appear (test with a focused text field)"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"How-do-I-show-HUD-on-the-full-screen-over-navigation-bar","text":"How do I show HUD on the full screen (over navigation bar)?","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Add the HUD to the window instead of the view controller’s view:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["if let window = view.window {","    HUD.show(to: window)","}"]},{"anchor":"Can-I-show-multiple-HUDs-simultaneously","text":"Can I show multiple HUDs simultaneously?","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Yes. Each ","type":"text"},{"code":"HUD.show(to:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" call creates a new HUD instance:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let hud1 = HUD.show(to: view, label: \"Step 1\")","let hud2 = HUD.show(to: view, label: \"Step 2\")"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"code":"HUD.hideAll(for:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to dismiss all at once.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"How-do-I-update-HUD-content-after-showing","text":"How do I update HUD content after showing?","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Access the HUD’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"contentView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to update labels, mode, or progress:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let hud = HUD.show(to: view)","\/\/ Later...","hud.contentView.label.text = \"Almost done...\"","hud.contentView.mode = .custom(checkmarkView)"]},{"anchor":"Appearance","text":"Appearance","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"anchor":"How-do-I-change-the-HUDs-background-transparency","text":"How do I change the HUD’s background transparency?","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["\/\/ Content card background","hud.contentView.color = UIColor.black.withAlphaComponent(0.7)","","\/\/ Full-screen overlay","hud.backgroundView.color = UIColor.black.withAlphaComponent(0.3)","hud.backgroundView.style = .solidColor"]},{"anchor":"How-do-I-make-the-HUD-largersmaller","text":"How do I make the HUD larger\/smaller?","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["\/\/ Set minimum size","hud.contentView.layout.minSize = CGSize(width: 150, height: 150)","","\/\/ Or adjust margins","hud.contentView.layout.hMargin = 30","hud.contentView.layout.vMargin = 30"]},{"anchor":"Can-I-use-SF-Symbols-as-custom-views","text":"Can I use SF Symbols as custom views?","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Yes:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let config = UIImage.SymbolConfiguration(pointSize: 30, weight: .medium)","let image = UIImage(systemName: \"wifi.exclamationmark\", withConfiguration: config)","let imageView = UIImageView(image: image)","HUD.showStatus(to: view, mode: .custom(imageView), label: \"No Connection\")"]},{"anchor":"Threading","text":"Threading","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"anchor":"Is-FlyHUD-thread-safe","text":"Is FlyHUD thread-safe?","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"All HUD APIs must be called on the main thread. The library uses ","type":"text"},{"code":"@MainActor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" isolation","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and debug assertions to enforce this. Background work should dispatch to main before","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"interacting with HUD:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["DispatchQueue.global().async {","    let result = heavyComputation()","    DispatchQueue.main.async {","        hud.contentView.label.text = result","        hud.hide()","    }","}"]},{"anchor":"Migration","text":"Migration","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"anchor":"How-do-I-migrate-from-MBProgressHUD","text":"How do I migrate from MBProgressHUD?","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"FlyHUD is inspired by MBProgressHUD with a modernized API:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"header":"row","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"MBProgressHUD","type":"text"}]}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"FlyHUD","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"MBProgressHUD.showAdded(to:animated:)","type":"codeVoice"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"HUD.show(to:animated:)","type":"codeVoice"}]}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MBProgressHUD.hide(for:animated:)"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"HUD.hide(for:animated:)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hud.mode = .text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"hud.contentView.mode = .text","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hud.label.text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hud.contentView.label.text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hud.progress"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hud.contentView.progress"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hud.bezelView"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hud.contentView"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hud.backgroundView"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hud.backgroundView"}],"type":"paragraph"}]]],"type":"table"}]}],"abstract":[{"text":"Frequently asked questions about FlyHUD.","type":"text"}],"references":{"doc://flyhud.FlyHUD/documentation/FlyHUD/CHANGELOG":{"abstract":[{"text"